294
00:34:44,167 --> 00:34:47,367
Yes, at the Sikh temple,
a couple of times may be.

295
00:34:47,875 --> 00:34:48,993
Just a couple?

296
00:34:49,083 --> 00:34:51,016
Maybe more, I don't remember.

297
00:34:51,333 --> 00:34:53,618
-How did he get the gun?
-I don't know.

298
00:34:53,708 --> 00:34:54,917
You don't know?

299
00:34:57,833 --> 00:34:58,958
That's all?

300
00:34:59,875 --> 00:35:01,155
Yes, that's all.

301
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:04,833
You will have to come with us, Sir.

302
00:35:10,750 --> 00:35:12,750
He is a small time businessman

303
00:35:13,708 --> 00:35:15,292
his name is Bawa.

304
00:35:15,667 --> 00:35:17,167
Fond of 'laddoos'

305
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:19,083
I mean sweets.

306
00:35:20,250 --> 00:35:22,910
Very passionate about
India's independence.

307
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:24,375
What else?

308
00:35:25,083 --> 00:35:28,868
I told you, Sir. He used to
visit the Sikh temple sometimes.

309
00:35:28,958 --> 00:35:31,542
Cut this nonsense. What else?

310
00:35:33,292 --> 00:35:35,208
I don't know much about him.

311
00:35:42,542 --> 00:35:44,625
Right, so what have we got?

312
00:35:45,250 --> 00:35:47,250
Well, we figured out he worked

313
00:35:47,375 --> 00:35:49,667
in a cotton mill in the Punjab…

314
00:35:49,958 --> 00:35:51,958
In about 1919.

315
00:35:52,125 --> 00:35:54,000
-Any Family?
-An orphan.

316
00:35:54,333 --> 00:35:57,410
His mother died when he was six.
His father soon after that.

317
00:35:57,500 --> 00:36:01,250
He and his brother, Ude,
they grew up in an orphanage.

318
00:36:02,792 --> 00:36:04,285
Any other relatives?

319
00:36:04,375 --> 00:36:07,042
Some cousins, but we are not sure yet.

320
00:36:07,833 --> 00:36:10,202
Immigration records show he entered London

321
00:36:10,292 --> 00:36:12,500
several times since 1933

322
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:16,958
using different names,
Sher Singh, Ude Singh,

323
00:36:17,083 --> 00:36:21,125
Udham Singh, Azad Singh and Frank Brazil.

324
00:36:21,750 --> 00:36:24,868
He first settled in a small
apartment in East London,

325
00:36:24,958 --> 00:36:28,077
and constantly shifted
residences almost every 6 months,

326
00:36:28,167 --> 00:36:31,495
from the East across to the
Southwest, at Bournemouth.

327
00:36:31,585 --> 00:36:35,821
Yeah. While here... he tried to
organize an international network

328
00:36:35,911 --> 00:36:40,883
of rebels for the Ghadr party making
contact with sources across Europe.

329
00:36:42,458 --> 00:36:46,243
There is a police complaint
against him in 1937

330
00:36:46,333 --> 00:36:50,941
for publicly beating another Indian
in a brawl in a bar in South London.

331
00:36:53,208 --> 00:36:56,285
He obtained a local peddler's
license working odd jobs

332
00:36:56,375 --> 00:36:58,055
as a stationery salesman,

333
00:36:58,292 --> 00:37:00,577
also as an extra on a movie set.

334
00:37:00,667 --> 00:37:01,827
I am a salesman.

335
00:37:01,917 --> 00:37:06,013
Sometime later, he is spotted
at a flea market selling lingerie,

336
00:37:06,292 --> 00:37:09,042
and he owns a Fiat car by now…

337
00:37:09,958 --> 00:37:12,993
Our last entry in the records
show him working as a welder

338
00:37:13,083 --> 00:37:15,350
in an iron factory in East London.

339
00:37:15,792 --> 00:37:17,577
This was about 6 months

340
00:37:17,667 --> 00:37:19,347
before the assassination.

341
00:37:35,667 --> 00:37:38,035
I heard this man was under our watch!

342
00:37:38,125 --> 00:37:39,618
How did he slip through?

343
00:37:39,708 --> 00:37:43,993
Well, he was put under watch nine years
ago Sir, when he left prison in India,

344
00:37:44,083 --> 00:37:48,285
and in that time he basically kept his
head down and we lost track of him.

345
00:37:48,375 --> 00:37:51,959
Few weeks ago we had a
tip off from the passport office,

346
00:37:52,167 --> 00:37:55,077
but by the time we had got
there, he had already fled.

347
00:37:55,167 --> 00:37:58,687
Are there any other conspirators?
Any other associates?

348
00:37:59,333 --> 00:38:02,743
There may be others waiting
to strike at high level targets.

349
00:38:02,833 --> 00:38:04,618
Have a look at the Germans,

350
00:38:04,708 --> 00:38:07,833
-we can't take any chances.
-Sir.

351
00:38:08,083 --> 00:38:10,000
-[GROANS]
-Who are you?

352
00:38:10,625 --> 00:38:12,160
What is your name?

353
00:38:12,250 --> 00:38:14,717
When is the next attack gonna happen?

354
00:38:20,625 --> 00:38:22,492
You thought you got them all

355
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:23,667
didn't you?

356
00:38:25,042 --> 00:38:26,458
Well you didn't!

357
00:38:30,042 --> 00:38:31,482
Only four bullets?

358
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:34,583
I had pumped in all six.

359
00:38:35,750 --> 00:38:37,202
Zetland is also dead, right?

360
00:38:37,292 --> 00:38:39,208
He said he fired six times.

361
00:38:39,417 --> 00:38:40,937
Isn't Zetland dead?

362
00:38:42,125 --> 00:38:43,500
Only O'Dwyer?

363
00:38:49,167 --> 00:38:50,625
I am gonna ask you

364
00:38:51,125 --> 00:38:52,417
one more time.

365
00:38:53,250 --> 00:38:56,000
Who are your associates?

366
00:38:59,250 --> 00:39:00,250
[GROANS]

367
00:39:03,125 --> 00:39:05,750
[LAUGHS]

368
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,875
I do not feel pain...

369
00:39:14,208 --> 00:39:15,667
I see death...

370
00:39:18,125 --> 00:39:19,500
feel no pain.

371
00:39:22,750 --> 00:39:23,750
Water...

372
00:39:24,667 --> 00:39:25,667
Water...

373
00:39:30,417 --> 00:39:33,833
[GRUNTING]

374
00:39:33,958 --> 00:39:35,660
You have eluded us for nine years.

375
00:39:35,750 --> 00:39:37,950
You must have made
some really nice friends.

376
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,560
Come on, tell me their names!

377
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:42,035
Tell me everything
about your collaborators.

378
00:39:42,125 --> 00:39:43,125
Come on...

379
00:39:48,542 --> 00:39:51,042
Tell me about the next target.

380
00:39:51,958 --> 00:39:55,750
[YELLS IN PAIN]

381
00:39:56,708 --> 00:39:57,910
[MUFFLED CRY]

382
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,300
Who...[PAINFUL SOBBING]

383
00:39:59,390 --> 00:40:01,515
Is the next attack for?

384
00:40:02,292 --> 00:40:03,972
Come on you can tell me.

385
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:07,083
[YELLS IN PAIN]

386
00:40:10,083 --> 00:40:11,292
Just try

387
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,467
just try and give us one little name.

388
00:40:14,667 --> 00:40:18,625
[YELLS IN PAIN]

389
00:40:25,083 --> 00:40:29,375
Tell me of all the other important
figures you were following.

390
00:40:39,208 --> 00:40:40,542
[SPEAKS RUSSIAN]

391
00:40:43,167 --> 00:40:44,447
Are you Russian?

392
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:48,333
Are these your papers?

393
00:40:51,125 --> 00:40:52,125
So.

394
00:40:52,708 --> 00:40:54,500
Did he have any visitors?

395
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:57,375
An Indian man...

396
00:41:00,250 --> 00:41:02,167
and a lady.

397
00:41:03,250 --> 00:41:04,500
An Indian lady?

398
00:41:05,958 --> 00:41:06,958
No.

399
00:41:08,583 --> 00:41:09,708
British?

400
00:41:10,250 --> 00:41:11,250
Yes.

401
00:41:18,018 --> 00:41:20,368
-Detective Thomson, Sir.
-Yes, put him through.

402
00:41:20,458 --> 00:41:22,958
Sir, he was frequently
visited by a British woman,

403
00:41:23,048 --> 00:41:25,368
an active member of the communist party,

404
00:41:25,458 --> 00:41:29,202
I suspect he may have established
links with other extremists through her.

405
00:41:29,292 --> 00:41:31,167
[CROWD PROTESTING]

406
00:41:31,333 --> 00:41:33,458
Down with imperialism!

407
00:41:39,167 --> 00:41:40,827
World in peace!

408
00:41:40,917 --> 00:41:42,833
Not in pieces!

409
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,000
Eileen

410
00:41:47,625 --> 00:41:48,905
Eileen Palmer...

411
00:41:49,167 --> 00:41:50,167
Eileen?

412
00:41:50,542 --> 00:41:51,542
I...

413
00:41:52,542 --> 00:41:54,333
I... Surat Ali... friend.

414
00:41:59,125 --> 00:42:00,645
Surat Ali's friend.

